## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of recent empirical data and the inherent biases present in the sources. The economic impact of minimum wage changes can vary significantly based on regional economic conditions, industry sectors, and the magnitude of the wage increase. Additionally, the long-term effects of minimum wage adjustments are complex and may not be fully captured in short-term studies. Further research is needed to explore these dynamics comprehensively.